' F-A two-guard ingress flow — a wire DeployDataProto.sig_algebra is rejected at
' the gRPC boundary if it contains a value/capability connective (⊕/&/!/?/⊸); the
' admitted funding_sig is then re-checked by is_funding_former() as a regression
' lock. Guard (1) ingress reject is LOAD-BEARING; guard (2) the gate predicate is
' the belt-and-suspenders regression lock (unreachable unless funding_sig is made
' non-total).
'
' Source of truth: docs/theory/cost-accounting-spec-alignment-audit.md
'                  (F-A; reject_capability_connectives casper_message.rs:1349,
'                   is_funding_former mod.rs:1846).
' Palette:  funding-input=mint #C8E6C9 · decisions=amber #FFE082
'           reject/error=red #EF9A9A · admit/credit=mint #C8E6C9
'   arrows: default control=grey #444444
' Render:  plantuml -tsvg docs/theory/diagrams/f-a-ingress-gate-flow.puml

@startuml f-a-ingress-gate-flow
!theme plain
skinparam defaultFontName "sans-serif"
skinparam ArrowColor                     #444444
skinparam ActivityBorderColor            #333333
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor        #FFFFFF
skinparam ActivityDiamondBackgroundColor #FFE082
skinparam ActivityDiamondBorderColor     #333333
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor            #FFF8E1
skinparam NoteBorderColor                #666666
title F-A two-guard ingress — ingress reject (load-bearing) + is_funding_former() (regression lock)

start
:wire DeployDataProto.sig_algebra; <<#C8E6C9>>
if (contains ⊕ / & / ! / ? / ⊸ ?) then (yes · capability connective)
  :from_proto_cosigned_with_sig_algebra\ncalls reject_capability_connectives; <<#EF9A9A>>
  :Err — refused at the gRPC boundary; <<#EF9A9A>>
  note right
    GUARD (1): the LOAD-BEARING guard.
    A value/capability connective never
    reaches the funding gate — it is
    refused with a crisp protocol error.
    F-A ingress reject (c).
  end note
  stop
else (no · only funding formers)
  :build Cosigned { wire_sig, pk }; <<#C8E6C9>>
  :derive funding_sig\n(Sig::Ground(pk) / And-fold of Sig::Ground(pkᵢ)); <<#C8E6C9>>
  if (funding_sig.is_funding_former() ?) then (yes · g | #P | s∘s)
    :admit to the gate\n(key Σ⟦s⟧, prove Σ ≥ Δ); <<#C8E6C9>>
    note right
      GUARD (2): the regression lock.
      envelope/funding derivation is already
      total to Ground/And, so this branch is
      always taken on valid traffic.
    end note
  else (no · non-funding former)
    :malformed — rejected\n(source_to_adt-failure path); <<#EF9A9A>>
    note right
      unreachable unless funding_sig is made
      non-total by a future change — exactly
      the regression F-A makes impossible
      (belt-and-suspenders).
    end note
    stop
  endif
endif
stop

legend bottom
  |= color |= meaning |
  |<#C8E6C9>| funding input / admitted to the gate (accounting) |
  |<#FFE082>| decision (ingress kind / funding-former predicate) |
  |<#EF9A9A>| reject / error (refused deploy) |
endlegend

@enduml
